{"type":"message","id":"3a98c37b","parentId":"229ffa04","timestamp":"2026-02-18T19:20:02.627Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Wed 2026-02-18 21:20 GMT+2] OPERATION: SYMBIOSIS (RUST LOGGER & SHELL-FREE).\n\n1.  **Logger 2.0 (`src/core/logger.py`):**\n    *   *Create/Edit:* Use `src/core/logger.py`.\n    *   *Import:* `import src.rust_core as rust`.\n    *   *Logic:* In `emit()`, use `rust.validate_checksum(record.msg)` to check `_dedup_cache`.\n    *   *Performance:* < 1μs overhead per log.\n\n2.  **Shell-Free Mode (`src/core/os_utils.py`):**\n    *   *Audit:* Scan for `subprocess`.\n    *   *Rewrite:*\n        *   `ls` -> `list(Path(p).iterdir())`\n        *   `rm` -> `Path(p).unlink()`\n        *   `grep` -> Python string check.\n    *   *Ban:* Remove `get_safe_command` (we don't need shell commands anymore).\n\n3.  **Auto-Doctor Hook (`src/main.py`):**\n    *   *Inject:* At top of `main()`.\n    *   *Code:*\n        ```python\n        try:\n            import src.rust_core as rust\n            # Warmup to ensure it's loaded\n            rust.validate_checksum(\"init\")\n            print(f\"🔩 Iron Core: ACTIVE (230ns)\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"FATAL: {e}\")\n            sys.exit(1)\n        ```\n\n4.  **Output:**\n    *   Logger code snippet.\n    *   OS Utils confirmation.\n    *   Main boot log check."}],"timestamp":1771442402626}}
{"type":"message","id":"291adcbe","parentId":"3a98c37b","timestamp":"2026-02-18T19:20:31.237Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Contemplating Code Changes**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm focused on the user's instructions regarding `src/core/logger.py`. The primary goal is integrating `rust_core` for checksum validation. I've broken down the tasks: importing the `rust` module, and then modifying the `emit` function. It seems straightforward, but I need to make sure the integration with `rust.validate_checksum()` is efficient and doesn't introduce any performance bottlenecks.\n\n\n**Evaluating Rust Integration**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI'm now shifting to the second directive, specifically to remove the shell dependency in `src/core/os_utils.py`. My initial assessment indicates the presence of subprocess calls, which I'll need to refactor. I'm exploring alternative approaches to achieve the same functionality without relying on shell commands. This will streamline the codebase.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771442431002_43","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/logger.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771442431108_44","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/os_utils.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771442431231_45","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/main.py"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4860,"output":146,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5006,"cost":{"input":0.00972,"output":0.001752,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011472}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771442402627}}
