{"type":"message","id":"2c8b21f4","parentId":"7fc59565","timestamp":"2026-02-18T19:21:49.145Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing Implementation Details**\n\nI realized my mistake. I misread the instructions regarding the import and checksum validation within the emit function. I need to make some adjustments to use the rust library functions correctly within the dedup_cache check. I'll need to re-examine the core/logger.py file.\n\n\n**Analyzing File Interactions**\n\nI'm now diving deeper into how `src/core/os_utils.py` interacts with the rest of the system. I need to replace `get_safe_command` and the shell commands it uses, but I'm concerned about breaking dependencies. My plan is to introduce the Python equivalents outlined in the instructions and ensure that the existing code uses them correctly. That will take some work, and I will have to touch other files.\n\n\n**Planning Replacement Strategy**\n\nI've clarified the intent of the instructions. The goal is to replace `get_safe_command` and shell commands *within* `src/core/os_utils.py` itself. I'll need to implement the Python equivalents for `ls`, `rm`, and `grep` as outlined. I also believe the user will address the callers in later tasks. Now, I'm defining the new functions in `src/core/os_utils.py`.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771442509142_48","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/os_utils.py","content":"\"\"\"\nShell-Free OS Utilities.\nReplaces shell commands with pure Python implementations to avoid subprocess overhead and security risks.\n\"\"\"\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import List, Union, Generator\n\ndef list_files(p: Union[str, Path]) -> List[Path]:\n    \"\"\"Replaces `ls` command.\"\"\"\n    return list(Path(p).iterdir())\n\ndef remove_file(p: Union[str, Path]) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Replaces `rm` command.\"\"\"\n    Path(p).unlink(missing_ok=True)\n\ndef grep_string(text: str, pattern: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Replaces `grep` command.\"\"\"\n    return pattern in text\n\n# DEPRECATED/BANNED:\n# get_safe_command is removed as we no longer support shell execution.\n"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":9587,"output":777,"cacheRead":8163,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10364,"cost":{"input":0.019174,"output":0.009324,"cacheRead":0.0016326000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.030130600000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771442491782}}
